%U A397712 51052570219128509334656640,102965864527102952655273305600,263231815662641254658699835508896
%N A397712 Number of acyclic digraphs (or DAGs) on n labeled nodes in which every node has in-degree at most 3.
%C A397712 Number of Bayesian network structures on n variables with at most 3 parents per variable.
%C A397712 k=3 member of the family A000272 (k=1, shifted), A397711 (k=2), A003024 (k unbounded). Agrees with A003024 for n <= 4; first divergence a(5) = 26566 versus 29281.
%C A397712 a(p) == 1 (mod p) for prime p, by the same cyclic-relabeling argument as A397711; unlike the k=2 case this does not extend to all odd n (a(9) == 7 mod 9).
%H A397712 Tyler Satchel Orden, <a href="/A397712/b397712.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..30</a>
%F A397712 Same level-decomposition sum as A397711 with F(p,q) = Sum_{i=1..3} (binomial(p+q,i) - binomial(q,i)).
%o A397712 (Python) # The program in A397711 with k=3.
%Y A397712 Cf. A003024 (no in-degree bound), A000272 (in-degree at most 1, shifted), A397711 (in-degree at most 2).
%K A397712 nonn,new
%O A397712 0,3
%A A397712 _Tyler Satchel Orden_, Jul 05 2026
